WEBVTT

00:01.001 --> 00:03.137
You're witnessing
the power of Empire.

00:03.171 --> 00:05.706
I'm Cookie Lyon, baby.
I'm unforgettable.

00:05.739 --> 00:07.308
Catch all-new episodes
Wednesdays.

00:07.341 --> 00:08.976
And check out
our other Fox programs--

00:09.009 --> 00:11.812
Star, The Gifted,
and Lethal Weapon.

00:11.845 --> 00:14.415
That was the best idea
you've had all day.

00:14.448 --> 00:15.549
Only on Fox.

00:17.685 --> 00:19.887
-Previously on Empire...
-I'm gonna spot you $10 mil

00:19.920 --> 00:20.988
for your 20 For 20.

00:21.021 --> 00:22.390
I could do another "Drip Drop"
in my sleep,

00:22.423 --> 00:23.557
but I need to go harder.

00:23.591 --> 00:24.692
She's not used to you yet.

00:24.725 --> 00:25.826
You were gone five months.

00:25.859 --> 00:26.827
PAMELA:
You don't need your attorney.

00:26.860 --> 00:28.062
I'm off duty.

00:28.096 --> 00:29.230
I trust you, right?

00:29.263 --> 00:30.664
My father has
a serious brain injury.

00:30.698 --> 00:31.832
We got to keep it under wraps.

00:31.865 --> 00:32.866
DIANA: Get a grip, Angelo.

00:32.900 --> 00:35.536
Put this floundering self-pity
to rest.

00:35.569 --> 00:36.870
It doesn't take
a rocket scientist

00:36.904 --> 00:39.073
to figure out
you're up to something.

00:39.107 --> 00:41.041
Was I a violent man?

00:41.075 --> 00:42.876
COOKIE:
I was gone for 17 years

00:42.910 --> 00:44.678
because I was in prison.

00:44.712 --> 00:46.046
I want to know everything.

00:47.047 --> 00:48.749
What's up, y'all?

00:48.782 --> 00:50.218
Welcome back to 106 & Park,
BET's top ten live.

00:50.251 --> 00:52.052
Now, I need y'all
to do me a favor.

00:52.086 --> 00:54.255
-Y'all ready to do me a favor?
-(applause and cheering on TV)

00:54.288 --> 00:57.558
That's my man up there.

00:57.591 --> 00:59.393
(on TV):
All right, mark down this date,

00:59.427 --> 01:02.430
this time, who you're with,
where you are, because

01:02.463 --> 01:04.198
this brother from Philly,
Lucious Lyon,

01:04.232 --> 01:05.966
-is making his TV debut...
-Change the channel.

01:05.999 --> 01:07.468
...and history.

01:07.501 --> 01:10.271
Uh, I-I was watching that.

01:10.304 --> 01:12.873
-Yeah, now we're watching this.
-CHYNA: Yo.

01:12.906 --> 01:16.043
-Don't even bother.
She got it on lock. -Ugh.

01:16.076 --> 01:17.478
Nah, man.

01:17.511 --> 01:18.779
Poundcake, right?

01:18.812 --> 01:21.048
LUCIOUS:
Wait a minute. Poundcake?

01:21.081 --> 01:23.417
Why-why was her name Poundcake?

01:23.451 --> 01:27.121
Look, how you want me
to tell the story? Huh?

01:27.155 --> 01:29.223
You want it blow by blow,
with me telling you

01:29.257 --> 01:31.058
how every bitch
got her wack-ass nickname,

01:31.091 --> 01:33.060
or you just gonna
let me tell the story?

01:33.093 --> 01:35.729
I mean, ever since I've been
out, you've never cared

01:35.763 --> 01:37.231
about my prison life.

01:37.265 --> 01:39.800
That was Lucious,
but I'm asking.

01:39.833 --> 01:42.170
It's important. I need to know
everything that happened.

01:42.203 --> 01:44.838
All right.

01:44.872 --> 01:47.908
Well, then, let me back up
and set the scene for you.

01:47.941 --> 01:51.078
I got real cool with Chyna

01:51.111 --> 01:53.281
and all the Philly girls,
of course.

01:53.314 --> 01:56.417
And, uh, we was cool
with the Latina chicks

01:56.450 --> 02:00.488
and was cool with the Chinese,
Japanese, or the Vietnamese.

02:00.521 --> 02:02.356
Whatever. The Asians.

02:02.390 --> 02:04.024
Child, the Asians.

02:04.057 --> 02:05.626
And we did not get along

02:05.659 --> 02:07.828
with them white chicks

02:07.861 --> 02:11.098
or the wild-ass Jamaicans.

02:11.131 --> 02:13.100
And Chyna had the...

02:13.133 --> 02:15.603
Ugh. She had a serious beef
with them D.C. girls, man.

02:15.636 --> 02:18.939
I don't know what it was, but

02:18.972 --> 02:21.141
they was wild, man.
They had nicknames

02:21.175 --> 02:25.112
like Yunk Yunk, Butterball,
and Poundcake.

02:25.145 --> 02:26.847
Look, I ain't trying
to disrespect you,

02:26.880 --> 02:29.450
but I'm gonna politely ask you
to turn that back

02:29.483 --> 02:31.785
-to BET 'cause I was watching
that. -Oh, well, since you asked

02:31.819 --> 02:33.687
so pretty,
I'll politely tell you no.

02:33.721 --> 02:36.123
Now move your bama ass
out my sight lines.

02:36.156 --> 02:39.126
-LUCIOUS: So, what'd you do?
-COOKIE: What you think I did?

02:39.159 --> 02:42.496
(groaning, indistinct shouting)

02:46.900 --> 02:50.137
Then she leaned down to my ear,
talking about,

02:50.170 --> 02:52.373
"You know why I'm in here?
For eating

02:52.406 --> 02:55.443
bitches like you for breakfast
and going on about my day."

02:58.846 --> 03:00.648
(Cookie yells)

03:00.681 --> 03:02.483
LUCIOUS:
And she cut you?

03:02.516 --> 03:04.017
She sure did.

03:04.051 --> 03:05.886
That wasn't my first fight,
Lucious.

03:05.919 --> 03:08.522
And it sure as hell
wasn't my last.

03:08.556 --> 03:11.225
But there were things
that happened to me in prison

03:11.259 --> 03:13.261
that cut deeper than a knife.

03:13.294 --> 03:15.396
Believe that.

03:15.429 --> 03:17.798
*

03:22.436 --> 03:25.739
-Lucious can't see me like this.
-So don't pick a fight

03:25.773 --> 03:28.909
with a chick named Poundcake
day before a visit.

03:28.942 --> 03:31.345
You're lucky nobody told,
or you'd be in the hole.

03:31.379 --> 03:33.614
Ouch. Can you...?
Do you know what you're doing?

03:33.647 --> 03:35.416
Are you questioning
my skill set?

03:35.449 --> 03:37.451
-I was good enough for Lil' Kim.
-Just go easy.

03:37.485 --> 03:38.886
-Come...
-Still sore.

03:38.919 --> 03:40.688
-What the hell is this?
-Nothing. -Nothing.

03:40.721 --> 03:43.190
-Huh?
-Nothing.

03:43.223 --> 03:45.225
-It's contraband.
-I know, but my husband's coming

03:45.259 --> 03:46.627
-to visit me today.
-Well, he's gonna have

03:46.660 --> 03:48.362
to see you
the way God made you--

03:48.396 --> 03:49.963
hood rat turned
into a punching bag.

03:49.997 --> 03:53.267
Wipe that off your face
before I throw you in the hole.

03:53.301 --> 03:55.569
Beauty tips, huh, Chyna?
(scoffs)

03:58.972 --> 04:00.941
COOKIE:
Yeah, she snitched,

04:00.974 --> 04:03.744
but her fat ass was the least
of my worries.

04:03.777 --> 04:06.647
(Cookie laughs)

04:06.680 --> 04:09.617
-(door opens) -Hey.
-LUCIOUS: Like I said, I'm gonna

04:09.650 --> 04:11.952
-take care of you for this.
-(Cookie sighs)

04:11.985 --> 04:14.855
-Hey. -I tried to get us
a little privacy, but...

04:16.824 --> 04:18.992
It's okay.

04:19.026 --> 04:20.994
-It's not o... What happened
to her face?! -I'm okay.

04:21.028 --> 04:23.063
-Lucious. Lucious, come here.
-(bangs on table)

04:23.096 --> 04:25.966
Look, our time is too precious
to be thinking about that.

04:25.999 --> 04:28.436
Look, I saw you on BET.

04:28.469 --> 04:30.938
You was so fine up there.
(laughs)

04:30.971 --> 04:33.240
-That was nothing.
-Oh, come on now, Lucious.

04:33.273 --> 04:36.243
Don't downplay it like that.
It was everything.

04:36.276 --> 04:39.012
It was exactly what AJ said--

04:39.046 --> 04:41.148
"Remember where you are
at this moment."

04:41.181 --> 04:43.517
So all I'm thinking about is
where I'm at and where you are.

04:43.551 --> 04:45.152
-And where...
-Hey, look, Lu...

04:45.185 --> 04:48.822
Lucious, I'm gonna be here
for a long time, okay?

04:48.856 --> 04:51.359
So might as well get used to it.

04:51.392 --> 04:54.294
I can deal with
what comes at me in here

04:54.328 --> 04:58.466
as long as I know you're out
there growing what we built.

04:58.499 --> 05:03.303
'Cause it's you and me--
Cookie and Lucious forever.

05:04.872 --> 05:07.608
Tell me about my babies.

05:07.641 --> 05:11.011
How are my babies doing?

05:11.044 --> 05:13.714
Well, Andre-- he's a little...

05:15.383 --> 05:17.518
Something not right.

05:17.551 --> 05:19.787
But Jamal-- he's been good,
and he...

05:19.820 --> 05:22.623
he wants to see you
for his birthday.

05:22.656 --> 05:24.525
Mm, no, Lucious.

05:24.558 --> 05:28.796
This ain't no place
for no boy for his birthday.

05:28.829 --> 05:32.866
Not unless he really want
to come, just, I guess.

05:32.900 --> 05:34.735
LUCIOUS:
I remember this.

05:37.738 --> 05:41.542
I brought Jamal
to see you the next time.

05:46.447 --> 05:48.982
Wait. Am I remembering this
correctly?

05:49.016 --> 05:52.386
You did bring Jamal, but...

05:52.420 --> 05:54.522
(indistinct chatter)

05:58.258 --> 06:01.128
Where's your father?

06:03.130 --> 06:05.766
LUCIOUS:
I never came back, did I?

06:05.799 --> 06:10.170
I guess it was just hard
for you to see me like that.

06:10.203 --> 06:12.172
It hurt.

06:12.205 --> 06:14.041
It hurt me to the core,

06:14.074 --> 06:17.411
but it made me self-sufficient,

06:17.445 --> 06:20.013
and, on the inside, it-it...
it made me strong.

06:20.047 --> 06:21.615
It made me hard.

06:21.649 --> 06:24.084
That's a sad lesson
to learn by yourself.

06:25.986 --> 06:28.088
He should have been there
for you.

06:28.121 --> 06:30.090
He should have.

06:30.123 --> 06:32.926
He should have
after everything you sacrificed.

06:32.960 --> 06:34.361
-He who?
-He.

06:34.394 --> 06:36.764
Him. Me. Lucious.

06:36.797 --> 06:40.868
If he loved you
half as much as he says he did,

06:40.901 --> 06:42.436
he would have never
abandoned you.

06:42.470 --> 06:45.973
He would have... put you first.

06:46.006 --> 06:49.643
I'm gonna be a better man
than he was.

06:49.677 --> 06:53.380
I'm gonna make it up to you
for everything he did wrong.

06:53.413 --> 06:56.383
(sighs)

06:56.416 --> 06:58.385
How can you make up
for something

06:58.418 --> 07:00.420
you don't even remember?

07:01.655 --> 07:04.424
(Cookie sighs)

07:04.458 --> 07:07.427
The sun's up.
I got to get ready for work.

07:07.461 --> 07:10.330
Okay, well, maybe you're right.

07:10.363 --> 07:13.066
Maybe I can't make up for
a yesterday I don't remember,

07:13.100 --> 07:16.069
but I can make today right.

07:16.103 --> 07:17.805
I can go down to Empire with you

07:17.838 --> 07:19.607
-and support you.
-No, no, no, no, no.

07:19.640 --> 07:22.776
Remember you said it didn't go
so well when Jamal took you.

07:22.810 --> 07:24.444
It wasn't that bad, and...

07:24.478 --> 07:27.014
-Okay, maybe it was.
-(both laugh)

07:27.047 --> 07:29.817
What I'm saying is,
I'd like to try it again.

07:29.850 --> 07:33.320
And I think, with your help,
I could make it through it.

07:33.353 --> 07:35.455
With my help?

07:38.358 --> 07:40.694
Okay. Well, then, let's go.

07:40.728 --> 07:43.864
CLAUDIA:
Where are we going?

07:43.897 --> 07:47.400
Dwight. Cookie. What'd I miss?

07:55.008 --> 07:56.777
-(cheering and applause)
-MAN: Welcome back.

07:56.810 --> 07:58.145
WOMAN:
Nice to have you back, Lucious.

07:58.178 --> 08:00.514
-Nice to have you back, Lucious.
-Welcome back, Lucious.

08:00.548 --> 08:02.149
-WOMAN: Looking good, Lucious.
-MAN 2: Happy to have you back.

08:02.182 --> 08:04.985
MAN 3:
Look out. Here he comes.

08:05.018 --> 08:06.987
If this gets too stressful
for Dwight, I'm gonna...

08:07.020 --> 08:09.523
I-I don't want
to hear Dwight stuff, okay?

08:09.557 --> 08:11.224
-Wow.
-This is the house

08:11.258 --> 08:13.827
that Lucious built.
Our house, our rules.

08:13.861 --> 08:16.129
-Lucious! Lucious, hi!
-(Lucious laughs)

08:16.163 --> 08:18.699
-It's so nice to see you.
-COOKIE: That's Becky.

08:18.732 --> 08:21.635
Becky was promoted
to head of A&R after

08:21.669 --> 08:24.171
-all those years
of being your assistant. -Wow.

08:24.204 --> 08:27.675
Well, you know what they say.
Cream always rises to the top.

08:27.708 --> 08:30.744
-Congratulations. -Thank you.
It is so good to see you.

08:30.778 --> 08:32.312
-You, too. -You say
I'm reckless, but I hid him

08:32.345 --> 08:33.914
when I brought him here.
What was the sense

08:33.947 --> 08:36.049
if Mom was just gonna walk him
in the front door?

08:36.083 --> 08:38.686
-Yeah. What the hell is she
doing? -These came for you.

08:38.719 --> 08:40.353
There's a card in there, too.

08:40.387 --> 08:42.189
Who they from?

08:42.222 --> 08:44.357
Yeah, thank you.
None of your business.

08:44.391 --> 08:46.994
"For tomorrow?"
Who you meeting with tomorrow?

08:47.027 --> 08:51.231
Hey. I need all hands on deck
keeping our family secret.

08:51.264 --> 08:54.201
-Lucious! What's up?!
How you doing? -Huh?

08:54.234 --> 08:55.903
-Good to see you!
-(laughing): Hi.

08:55.936 --> 08:58.205
Welcome back.
Where your suit?

08:58.238 --> 08:59.907
You looking like a...
hippie and stuff.

08:59.940 --> 09:01.541
But you look good.
You look good.

09:01.575 --> 09:03.944
-Why didn't you keep him home?
-Because he wants to be

09:03.977 --> 09:06.614
a part of all of this,
and I couldn't say no.

09:06.647 --> 09:08.616
So we'll just keep it
short and sweet.

09:08.649 --> 09:11.218
We'll have him listen
to Hakeem's song,

09:11.251 --> 09:13.553
-and we'll send him home
with Nurse Ratchet. -Well, Mom,

09:13.587 --> 09:15.088
Hakeem's not even here.
He's at his house

09:15.122 --> 09:16.523
arguing with Anika
about Bella's birthday.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.258
Uh-uh, uh-uh-uh.
Tell him to get

09:18.291 --> 09:20.694
his ass down here.
He can bring my grandbaby.

09:20.728 --> 09:22.730
Can y'all believe
she having a birthday already?

09:22.763 --> 09:25.032
-(laughs) -Yeah. Time flies.
-COOKIE: I know.

09:25.065 --> 09:27.334
Come on.
I need help with your dad.

09:31.171 --> 09:33.641
-(classical music playing)
-DIANA: Amnesia?

09:33.674 --> 09:35.643
Like in a soap opera.

09:35.676 --> 09:38.946
(laughs)
He don't even know his name.

09:38.979 --> 09:40.313
He wants them
to call him Dwight.

09:40.347 --> 09:41.782
-You're not serious.
-I'm serious.

09:41.815 --> 09:44.718
He has migraines, outbursts.

09:44.752 --> 09:48.321
He treats his nurse like family
and his family like strangers.

09:48.355 --> 09:50.958
Hakeem never breathed
a word of this.

09:50.991 --> 09:52.926
And how did you get
this information?

09:52.960 --> 09:55.062
In bed with your catamite?

09:55.095 --> 09:57.564
-(laughs)
-Excuse me? Catamite?

09:57.597 --> 09:59.466
DIANA: It's a line
from an Anthony Burgess novel.

09:59.499 --> 10:02.970
Okay, so you found your razor,
you made it to your meeting.

10:03.003 --> 10:05.072
That does not entitle you
to be a snob.

10:05.105 --> 10:07.407
Right. I'm just saying,

10:07.440 --> 10:10.010
how do we know
he's not playing you... cuz?

10:10.043 --> 10:13.413
Because I'm not like you... cuz.

10:13.446 --> 10:16.283
'Cause when I sleep with a Lyon,
I get the goods.

10:16.316 --> 10:17.851
-And there it is.
-DIANA: Thank you for sharing.

10:17.885 --> 10:20.520
-That's good work.
-Thank you.

10:20.553 --> 10:21.955
Much appreciated, and, Angelo,

10:21.989 --> 10:23.857
the running commentary
from the sidelines

10:23.891 --> 10:25.358
is interesting.

10:25.392 --> 10:27.194
But why don't you do
something useful?

10:28.228 --> 10:30.163
-Really.
-(Warren laughs)

10:30.197 --> 10:31.364
(sighs)

10:33.466 --> 10:35.335
You want to use some ear plugs?

10:35.368 --> 10:39.272
No. No, I want to participate
and not really hide.

10:39.306 --> 10:40.774
-But thank you.
-HAKEEM: Hit it, Rekkhan.

10:40.808 --> 10:42.710
-(music plays)
* Shut up, shut up

10:42.743 --> 10:44.444
* Hey, shut up, trick,
that means don't talk *

10:44.477 --> 10:46.179
* Don't call me,
my phone's off *

10:46.213 --> 10:47.314
* I'm good now,
that's your loss *

10:47.347 --> 10:49.116
* I'm self-made, my own boss

10:49.149 --> 10:50.884
* Now who's trippin'?
My roof missin' *

10:50.918 --> 10:53.120
* My jewels glistening, who's
listening? Ya heard that *

10:53.153 --> 10:55.823
* My new whip got two engines,
that's too expensive *

10:55.856 --> 10:57.657
* Lower ya voice 'cause I don't
wanna hear what you sayin' *

10:57.691 --> 10:59.192
* I'm tired of talkin'

10:59.226 --> 11:01.862
* Ain't no conversation,
hope you understand *

11:01.895 --> 11:03.496
* I don't like you,
you, you, you *

11:03.530 --> 11:06.867
* You're cool,
but the rest of y'all... *

11:06.900 --> 11:10.170
* Shut up, bitch, ooh...

11:10.203 --> 11:13.874
* Shut up, shut up

11:13.907 --> 11:16.143
* Uh...

11:16.176 --> 11:18.979
-(music stops)
-What you think about that, Dad?

11:19.012 --> 11:22.049
Does it remind you of Jay-Z
on Blueprint?

11:22.082 --> 11:26.019
I mean, I don't know much
about architecture,

11:26.053 --> 11:27.420
but I was really inspired by

11:27.454 --> 11:29.222
the amount of effort
you've put into that.

11:29.256 --> 11:31.558
BECKY: Okay, Hakeem,
that definitely was not

11:31.591 --> 11:33.193
the song you were supposed
to be working on.

11:33.226 --> 11:35.562
'Cause I got to keep it real,
track by track.

11:35.595 --> 11:37.497
Exposing hypocrisy in democracy.

11:37.530 --> 11:39.733
What do you think, Ma?

11:39.767 --> 11:42.669
Uh, there were some nice things
in it, son.

11:42.702 --> 11:44.504
You know what? Why don't you go
get something to eat?

11:44.537 --> 11:47.340
Come on, y'all. Marcel.
And, uh, let us discuss it.

11:47.374 --> 11:49.743
All right, Dad.

11:49.777 --> 11:52.012
(indistinct chatter)

11:52.045 --> 11:53.513
What was that?

11:53.546 --> 11:55.916
-I do not know.
-What? You didn't like that?

11:55.949 --> 11:58.018
I just bet $100 million
of other peoples' money

11:58.051 --> 12:00.754
that Empire would showcase
a legacy

12:00.788 --> 12:02.522
with that boy's album
as the Alpha

12:02.555 --> 12:04.091
and Jamal as the Omega.

12:04.124 --> 12:06.226
But guess what.
That wasn't it.

12:06.259 --> 12:09.096
I mean, I really didn't like
the-the nature of the song,

12:09.129 --> 12:11.231
you know,
but he was so passionate

12:11.264 --> 12:12.966
in how he was delivering that.

12:13.000 --> 12:15.702
BECKY: You know, Lucious,
you just came back

12:15.735 --> 12:18.105
at the perfect time
because you always come up

12:18.138 --> 12:20.240
with some crazy, Machiavellian
scheme to save the day.

12:20.273 --> 12:21.741
Like, remember that time

12:21.775 --> 12:24.211
Diddy canceled on us
24 hours right before

12:24.244 --> 12:26.246
-the Radio City Music Hall show?
-Uh, no, no.

12:26.279 --> 12:27.915
Not-not, uh, Radio City.

12:27.948 --> 12:29.316
Um, just last night, Dad was

12:29.349 --> 12:30.750
telling me
about one of the concerts

12:30.784 --> 12:32.485
he had in Philly,
and you're right, Pop.

12:32.519 --> 12:34.721
What you did there was exactly
what you said we should do

12:34.754 --> 12:36.556
with 20 For 20.

12:36.589 --> 12:38.291
Oh.

12:40.360 --> 12:43.897
Um...

12:43.931 --> 12:45.132
exactly.

