25:49.749 --> 25:52.084
and she wasn't in there
long enough to break a nail.

25:52.118 --> 25:54.186
Look, Lucious is leaving.
He just came to stop by.

25:54.220 --> 25:56.188
-I wanted to see Bella.
-I'm sorry I did not come

25:56.222 --> 25:57.890
see you in the hospital.
I'm sure you would have come

25:57.924 --> 25:59.592
to see me in jail
if you had been able to.

25:59.626 --> 26:01.393
After all, you are the reason
that I was there.

26:06.398 --> 26:09.268
Listen, I'm...

26:09.301 --> 26:12.204
Anika, I'm sorry
for anything I did wrong to you.

26:12.238 --> 26:14.807
I really am.

26:18.845 --> 26:21.247
A sincere apology?

26:21.280 --> 26:22.314
(chuckling):
Wow.

26:22.348 --> 26:23.482
Lucious, what is this for?

26:23.515 --> 26:24.817
For, uh...

26:24.851 --> 26:26.252
forcing me into a sham marriage?

26:26.285 --> 26:27.887
Or for ripping my child

26:27.920 --> 26:29.121
out of my arms for six months?

26:29.155 --> 26:30.389
Who the hell you think you are

26:30.422 --> 26:31.590
-to judge anybody?
-Andre!

26:31.624 --> 26:32.825
-What, you forgot?
Did you forget? -Andre!

26:32.859 --> 26:34.426
-Do you need me to remind you?
-Calm down!

26:34.460 --> 26:35.427
LUCIOUS:
Orient yourself.

26:35.461 --> 26:36.663
(Bella crying)

26:36.696 --> 26:37.897
-Just breathe.
-Just breathe.

26:37.930 --> 26:38.998
-HAKEEM: Just calm down.
-LUCIOUS: Breathe.

26:39.031 --> 26:41.634
Orient yourself around the room

26:41.668 --> 26:43.235
and find another way to express

26:43.269 --> 26:46.806
-what you're feeling.
-(sighs)

26:46.839 --> 26:48.140
HAKEEM:
Just breathe, Dre.

26:48.174 --> 26:49.842
(inhales deeply)

26:49.876 --> 26:51.477
(exhales)

26:51.510 --> 26:53.846
You're not the only person
in this family

26:53.880 --> 26:55.614
to forget things.

26:57.049 --> 26:59.618
Something else happened
the day Bella was born.

27:03.990 --> 27:07.126
Rhonda.

27:07.159 --> 27:09.962
(whispering):
Oh, I'm so sorry.

27:09.996 --> 27:11.964
Somebody sent me flowers today.

27:11.998 --> 27:13.532
(sighs)

27:13.565 --> 27:16.535
I thought it was one of you,
but...

27:16.568 --> 27:18.137
(exhales)

27:18.170 --> 27:20.139
I should have known better.

27:20.172 --> 27:22.208
I told you my wife died, Pop,

27:22.241 --> 27:25.111
but I didn't tell you how.

27:25.144 --> 27:26.612
Screaming.

27:26.645 --> 27:29.181
Every bone in her body...

27:29.215 --> 27:30.883
broken.

27:32.218 --> 27:34.320
And the last face she saw,

27:34.353 --> 27:35.822
it was...

27:37.423 --> 27:40.192
But because you all felt
that protecting family secrets

27:40.226 --> 27:41.994
was more important
than telling the truth,

27:42.028 --> 27:43.195
she got away with murder.

27:43.229 --> 27:44.897
And now here you are,

27:44.931 --> 27:48.134
planning
her baby's birthday party

27:48.167 --> 27:49.969
while my family,

27:50.002 --> 27:51.537
-my family...
-(screaming)

27:51.570 --> 27:53.672
-rots in the ground!
-Andre! (sighs)

27:53.706 --> 27:57.343
But that's how it goes, Pop.

27:58.577 --> 27:59.912
That's how it always goes
for me.

27:59.946 --> 28:02.148
(Bella crying)

28:02.181 --> 28:04.183
(exhales)

28:14.761 --> 28:16.495
You were right. I was wrong.

28:16.528 --> 28:18.564
Oh.

28:18.597 --> 28:19.932
Is there...

28:19.966 --> 28:23.335
is there something
that-that you need?

28:23.369 --> 28:26.672
Just a big, fat "I told you so."

28:26.705 --> 28:28.007
(chuckles)

28:28.040 --> 28:31.510
Well, he was, um...

28:31.543 --> 28:34.213
disoriented when he got home.

28:34.246 --> 28:36.215
We were gonna do
some somatic work,

28:36.248 --> 28:37.884
but I just put him to bed.

28:37.917 --> 28:41.253
I just wanted Lucious'
first day back to Empire

28:41.287 --> 28:43.589
to be amazing.

28:43.622 --> 28:45.892
Guess he wasn't ready.

28:45.925 --> 28:48.560
I did read the book you gave me.

28:48.594 --> 28:51.463
-Great. -And there's
a section in it about, uh,

28:51.497 --> 28:53.933
identifying, uh, the crossroads?

28:53.966 --> 28:55.601
I'm looking for it with him.

28:55.634 --> 28:57.736
We're using lucid dreaming.

28:57.770 --> 28:59.638
I think I know
Lucious' crossroads.

28:59.671 --> 29:01.707
I've been there.

29:01.740 --> 29:03.075
Seen it.

29:03.109 --> 29:04.476
I'm-I'm thinking
about taking him.

29:04.510 --> 29:06.145
-Like it says in the book...
-Oh, no.

29:06.178 --> 29:07.446
Please, please don't.

29:07.479 --> 29:08.815
Don't take him there.

29:08.848 --> 29:11.150
It's too soon.

29:11.183 --> 29:14.420
Listen, Cookie, this really
could be a critical tool

29:14.453 --> 29:17.656
once his core identity
is more stable.

29:17.689 --> 29:19.358
But in the right time.

29:20.927 --> 29:24.530
Tell me about it.

29:25.597 --> 29:29.101
Well, it's back in Philly.

29:29.135 --> 29:32.104
It's a lion statue in the hood.

29:32.138 --> 29:34.606
And Lucious slept under it

29:34.640 --> 29:36.909
the first night he was homeless.

29:36.943 --> 29:38.845
Back when he was, uh...

29:38.878 --> 29:40.446
Dwight Walker.

29:40.479 --> 29:43.349
He was only nine years old.

29:46.152 --> 29:47.820
Don't you think
it's a little late in the game

29:47.854 --> 29:49.521
for you to be changing
your tracks now, baby?

29:49.555 --> 29:52.091
Yeah, but I can't help that.
I mean, Tory and I

29:52.124 --> 29:53.592
kind of tweaked the lyrics
last night,

29:53.625 --> 29:54.861
but it's still bothering me.

29:54.894 --> 29:57.296
Let me see.

29:58.730 --> 30:01.300
Well, unless you secretly been
into Taylor Swift all this time,

30:01.333 --> 30:02.969
maybe it's the line
about smeared red lips

30:03.002 --> 30:04.036
and smudged eyeliner.

30:04.070 --> 30:05.637
What am I supposed to do?

30:05.671 --> 30:07.673
I'm supposed to sing about
scruffy faces in the morning?

30:07.706 --> 30:08.941
No, I didn't say all of that.

30:08.975 --> 30:10.376
But, you know, I don't know.

30:10.409 --> 30:13.445
True. I mean, honestly, why not?

30:13.479 --> 30:14.847
What?

30:14.881 --> 30:17.649
Well, scruffy faces, no.

30:17.683 --> 30:19.852
But it's been feeling fake,

30:19.886 --> 30:21.954
and if I'm gonna sing
about love,

30:21.988 --> 30:24.023
I should sing
about the way that I love.

30:25.257 --> 30:26.725
Love?

30:26.758 --> 30:28.694
They don't call it
"making like," do they?

30:28.727 --> 30:30.362
(playing piano)

30:39.605 --> 30:41.173
PORSHA: We just heard all
the best Empire has to offer.

30:41.207 --> 30:43.309
-Still not good enough.
-What in the hell is this?

30:43.342 --> 30:45.011
So, what-what-what do we do now?

30:45.044 --> 30:47.379
Well, thank the music gods

30:47.413 --> 30:49.515
Jamal actually agreed
to come in and audition.

30:49.548 --> 30:51.250
And he's doing a duet.

30:51.283 --> 30:53.319
With who?

30:53.352 --> 30:55.254
Oh, no, no.

30:55.287 --> 30:57.856
No, Snow White.
Didn't I tell you no?

30:57.890 --> 30:59.691
Cookie, just listen
to the song, okay?

30:59.725 --> 31:01.193
It'll knock the rocks off
your little collar there.

31:01.227 --> 31:03.262
No! Jamal,

31:03.295 --> 31:04.563
-can you fix this?
-JAMAL: Yo, I-I'm...

31:04.596 --> 31:05.764
I'm sorry for, um, being late.

31:05.797 --> 31:08.500
I was working on the song
all night long.

31:08.534 --> 31:10.669
Tory, I love you, you know I do,

31:10.702 --> 31:12.204
but I had to take you
off the song.

31:12.238 --> 31:13.672
-What? -Yes.
I'm trying to make an album

31:13.705 --> 31:15.541
-full of love songs. I'm sorry.
-What?

31:15.574 --> 31:17.009
-And that can't include me?
-No, it can't.

31:17.043 --> 31:18.710
I'm sorry.

31:18.744 --> 31:21.013
Take your little song.
I don't need you anyway.

31:21.047 --> 31:22.381
I'm done.
You guys are ridiculous.

31:22.414 --> 31:24.250
-This is just absolutely absurd.
-All right, she mad at me...

31:24.283 --> 31:25.517
Bye-bye. Thank you.

31:25.551 --> 31:27.053
(clears throat)

31:27.086 --> 31:29.922
Anyway,
I've got to make music that...

31:29.956 --> 31:31.357
If it's gonna be a love song,

31:31.390 --> 31:32.624
it's got to reflect
the way that I love.

31:32.658 --> 31:34.060
So I'm going to sing a duet,

31:34.093 --> 31:35.227
but it's gonna be with a man.

31:35.261 --> 31:36.895
Warren?

31:36.929 --> 31:37.964
Warren?

31:37.997 --> 31:39.631
Uh-uh. Warren is a lawyer.

31:39.665 --> 31:41.433
He is not an Empire artist.

31:41.467 --> 31:42.734
Becky, chill out, okay?

31:42.768 --> 31:44.370
'Cause, first of all,
you know the boy can sing.

31:44.403 --> 31:46.905
-He's all right. -He's just
gonna demo it for now.

31:46.939 --> 31:48.107
-Just listen.
-COOKIE: Okay, well,

31:48.140 --> 31:49.441
can y'all hurry up?
You're wasting my time.

31:49.475 --> 31:50.609
I'm on deadline.

31:50.642 --> 31:53.312
Don't pay attention to anybody.
Just sing to me.

31:53.345 --> 31:56.115
-Go! -Looking pretty nervous
