36:28.687 --> 36:31.523
* Pills and thrills
and daffodils *

36:31.557 --> 36:36.194
* Will kill,
hang tough, children *

36:36.228 --> 36:39.798
* He's comin', he's comin'

36:41.066 --> 36:43.269
* He's comin'

36:43.302 --> 36:45.804
(high-pitched):
* He's comin'!

36:51.543 --> 36:54.313
(applause and cheering)

36:57.416 --> 37:00.386
(guitar solo)

37:03.989 --> 37:07.225
Yeah!
Happy birthday, Bella.

37:21.106 --> 37:23.675
(song ends)

37:33.685 --> 37:35.354
(grunting)

37:36.488 --> 37:37.923
(gunshot)

37:40.292 --> 37:42.794
Hey.

37:42.828 --> 37:44.763
I thought you were supposed
to be getting ready

37:44.796 --> 37:46.565
for Bella's party.

37:46.598 --> 37:50.302
That man that Cookie
wants me to be--

37:50.336 --> 37:54.005
he keeps trying to come back
in my head. Uh...

37:54.039 --> 37:56.141
I don't want to be him.

37:56.174 --> 37:58.410
He's not a good person.
I don't like him.

37:58.444 --> 38:02.080
Dwight?

38:02.113 --> 38:05.417
Hey, just because you know him

38:05.451 --> 38:08.587
doesn't mean
you have to become him.

38:08.620 --> 38:10.622
This is a really
important moment.

38:10.656 --> 38:12.824
You're at a crossroads.

38:12.858 --> 38:15.661
Let me help you choose
a different path.

38:17.663 --> 38:20.031
Come with me.

38:24.803 --> 38:27.939
* It's your birthday, your
birthday, your birthday... *

38:27.973 --> 38:29.875
-This is amazing. Oh, I'm sorry.
I got to go -I thought you...

38:29.908 --> 38:31.610
-say something.
-* Your birthday

38:31.643 --> 38:33.712
* Your birth, it's your
birthday, your birthday... *

38:33.745 --> 38:35.881
I'm so sorry that we forgot

38:35.914 --> 38:38.316
how sad this day was for you,
for all of us.

38:38.350 --> 38:39.951
It's not Bella's fault.

38:39.985 --> 38:42.320
This family needs to find light
where it can, so...

38:42.354 --> 38:44.956
Yeah.

38:44.990 --> 38:48.394
Dre, look,
you know we love you, right?

38:48.427 --> 38:51.129
We're not a family
without you.

38:51.162 --> 38:52.498
We need you.

38:52.531 --> 38:55.667
Maybe Pop was onto something

38:55.701 --> 38:57.836
with this whole, you know,
kumbaya business.

38:57.869 --> 38:59.471
Yeah, he was.
You know what?

38:59.505 --> 39:01.873
I owe him an apology.
Where is he?

39:01.907 --> 39:03.509
I don't know,
I haven't seen him.

39:03.542 --> 39:05.310
Okay, glad to see you, though.

39:05.343 --> 39:08.514
-Okay. Porsha?
-* Better recognize.

39:08.547 --> 39:10.749
-For you, ma'am.
-Thank you, James.

39:10.782 --> 39:12.150
You're welcome.

39:12.183 --> 39:15.487
Hmm. I cannot wait
to see what is happening

39:15.521 --> 39:17.222
in the Metro Observer.

39:17.255 --> 39:19.558
Ooh!

39:19.591 --> 39:21.159
-Wow.
-Huh.

39:21.192 --> 39:22.728
They work fast.

39:22.761 --> 39:24.896
Well, they owe me more favors
than I can count.

39:24.930 --> 39:26.998
Enjoy the sneak preview.

39:27.032 --> 39:30.301
The final edition
will be lethal.

39:47.886 --> 39:51.056
If you're here to arrest me,
you could at least do it

39:51.089 --> 39:54.526
in some place other
than my niece's birthday party.

39:54.560 --> 39:57.896
I was looking at your files.

39:57.929 --> 40:00.098
I saw that today is the day
your wife...

40:02.768 --> 40:05.537
I've already been
incredibly unprofessional,

40:05.571 --> 40:08.239
and I'm probably an idiot
for it,

40:08.273 --> 40:10.809
but I thought
you might be in for a tough day.

40:10.842 --> 40:13.111
You sent the flowers.

40:13.144 --> 40:16.147
CHICKEN:
What's up, Dre?

40:16.181 --> 40:19.485
-What's up?
-(chuckles) Okay.

40:19.518 --> 40:22.621
Let's get the hell out of here.

40:28.159 --> 40:29.661
-Oh, man, that's shady.
-COOKIE: Wait a minute.

40:29.695 --> 40:31.797
-What?
-What are you doing?

40:31.830 --> 40:33.832
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
Before we open up any gifts,

40:33.865 --> 40:36.401
where is Anika? We-we can't
open up gifts until her...

40:36.434 --> 40:38.670
Mom, we don't need Anika
to open gifts up.

40:38.704 --> 40:40.338
I don't know, y'all.
All these gifts, I swear.

40:40.371 --> 40:42.007
North West and them,
they about to call us gauche.

40:42.040 --> 40:44.743
COOKIE: No. Shut up. North West
ain't got nothing on Bella Lyon.

40:44.776 --> 40:46.745
Bella, look.
(whoops)

40:46.778 --> 40:48.614
Bella, boo. There you are.

40:48.647 --> 40:52.484
Happy birthday, Bella.

40:52.518 --> 40:54.185
Can't believe
it's already been a year.

40:54.219 --> 40:57.322
-Uh, what the hell are you
doing here? -I invited him.

40:57.355 --> 40:59.324
Oh. So I see you still like
my sloppy seconds.

40:59.357 --> 41:01.693
(scoffs):
Oh, Cookie.

41:01.727 --> 41:03.194
Though Anika may be more
my taste

41:03.228 --> 41:05.864
-than your ghetto ass
ever was, she... -Ha.

41:05.897 --> 41:07.666
-No, what you come up in here
with this? -No, no, sit down.

41:07.699 --> 41:10.268
-He ain't worth it. -We didn't
come here as a couple.

41:10.301 --> 41:12.470
I came with a gift,
though not for Bella.

41:12.504 --> 41:16.341
This gift is for...
the baby's father.

41:16.374 --> 41:20.345
So this is how you treat us
after we include you?

41:20.378 --> 41:22.180
Thank you for including me

41:22.213 --> 41:24.650
in my own daughter's
birthday party, Cookie.

41:24.683 --> 41:26.351
But if there's anything
that I've learned

41:26.384 --> 41:28.453
in the last few years,
very personally,

41:28.486 --> 41:30.822
is that the Lyons
will destroy everything

41:30.856 --> 41:32.558
-that they put their hands on.
-Mm.

41:32.591 --> 41:36.962
Therefore, I will not allow you
to destroy my daughter.

41:36.995 --> 41:40.198
Angelo is here
as my attorney.

41:40.231 --> 41:43.134
I am suing for sole custody
of Bella.

41:43.168 --> 41:46.738
-Ugh.
-(Bella crying)

41:48.874 --> 41:50.842
Here are our demands.

41:50.876 --> 41:52.243
Happy reading.

41:52.277 --> 41:54.746
Happy birthday.

41:59.851 --> 42:01.887
(indistinct conversations)

42:12.964 --> 42:15.066
Where... where are we?

42:15.100 --> 42:17.603
This is the crossroads
where little Dwight Walker

42:17.636 --> 42:20.271
became Lucious Lyon.

42:37.656 --> 42:40.959
Do you see him there?

42:44.763 --> 42:47.298
He looks so sad and alone.

42:47.332 --> 42:49.434
I understand.
I know what that feels like.

42:52.904 --> 42:55.874
To be sad and alone.

42:55.907 --> 42:59.244
But he doesn't ever have
to be alone again.

42:59.277 --> 43:01.813
If you want to change that,

43:01.847 --> 43:04.282
you can choose a different path
right now.

43:04.315 --> 43:06.952
It's up to you.

43:06.985 --> 43:09.087
Would you come with me?

43:09.120 --> 43:12.357
Yes, if you want me to.

43:48.026 --> 43:49.160
Yeah.

43:49.194 --> 43:51.162
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

43:53.464 --> 43:54.800
* Uh *

43:54.833 --> 43:56.334
I guess I used to
be a scary person.

43:56.367 --> 43:58.269
* Whoo *

43:58.303 --> 44:01.206
You hurry up and fix my man,
or we gonna have a problem.

44:01.239 --> 44:05.043
They're gonna turn me
into a monster.

44:05.076 --> 44:08.379
You and me,
Cookie and Lucious forever.

44:08.413 --> 44:12.884
He doesn't even know his name.
He treats his nurse like family
and his family like strangers.

44:12.918 --> 44:14.652
We get knocked down,
we get back up.

44:16.354 --> 44:17.723
Let the games begin.

44:17.756 --> 44:20.726
ANNOUNCER:
Empire. Wednesdays on Fox.

44:20.759 --> 44:23.328
* Say it like
You really mean it *
